1. Project Overview

Sentix Tinder is a mobile-first analytics dashboard designed to present sentiment analysis results derived from Tinder app store reviews. The interface gives product stakeholders an at-a-glance view of user sentiment, aspect-level breakdowns, keyword trends, and anomalies — all in a clean, brand-aligned mobile UI.

The Stitch prototype contains four primary screens delivered in three visual variants (Dark v1, Dark v2 / Glassmorphism, and Light), totalling twelve HTML files. This document serves as the canonical design reference for development handoff.

1.1 Purpose of This Document
•Define the component inventory, layout rules, and interaction behaviours for each screen
•Document the design token system (colours, typography, spacing, effects)
•Capture the three visual variants and the rules governing when each is applied
•Provide a development handoff checklist and open decisions log

1.2 Design Goals
#	Goal	Rationale
G1	Mobile-first layout	All screens target 390px wide viewport (iPhone 14 Pro class)
G2	Brand coherence	Tinder pink/orange gradient anchors the visual identity throughout
G3	Data clarity	Complex NLP output must be scannable in under 5 seconds per screen
G4	Accessibility	Light theme variant targets WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1 minimum)
G5	Theme flexibility	Dark and light themes share identical structure; only tokens differ



