5. Navigation & Information Architecture

5.1 Screen Flow
The app follows a shallow two-level navigation model. The Dashboard Overview acts as the hub; all other screens are reached via the bottom navigation bar (v2) or from alert/insight cards.

Entry Point	Destination	Trigger
Dashboard Overview	Aspect Analysis	Tap an aspect card or the Aspect icon in bottom nav
Dashboard Overview	Review Explorer	Tap 'Reviews' in bottom nav, or tap Mismatch Alert banner
Dashboard Overview	Keyword Insights	Tap 'Keywords' or any word cloud teaser card (future)
Review Explorer	Review Detail	Tap individual review card (future screen)
Any screen	Dashboard	Tap 'Stats' (first item) in bottom nav

5.2 Bottom Navigation Bar (Dark v2)
Tab	Icon (Material Symbols)	Route
Stats	dashboard	/dashboard (active default)
Reviews	forum	/reviews
Alerts	notifications	/alerts
Settings	settings	/settings
Note: The bottom nav is present only in Dark v2. Dark v1 uses inline navigation via back arrows. Adopt the v2 nav for production across all variants.

