7. Responsive Design Constraints

The prototype is designed exclusively for mobile viewports. Desktop usage is not in scope for v1.0.

Breakpoint	Target Devices	Notes
375px — 390px	iPhone SE / iPhone 14 Pro	Primary design target. All screens tested at 390px.
360px — 375px	Android mid-range	Ensure KPI grid doesn't overflow. Reduce card padding to p-3 if needed.
412px — 430px	Pixel 8 / iPhone 15 Plus	Extra horizontal space — max-w-md wrapper recommended to cap at 448px.
≥ 768px (tablet)	iPad / tablet browsers	Out of scope v1. May require layout refactor to 2-column grid in future.

8. Accessibility Considerations

Area	Requirement
Colour contrast	Light theme: all text on white backgrounds must meet 4.5:1 WCAG AA. Pink #FE3C72 on white = 3.9:1 — use only for decorative text, not body copy.
Touch targets	All interactive elements (chips, cards, nav icons) must be ≥ 44×44px per Apple HIG / Android guidelines.
ARIA labels	Back button → aria-label='Go back'; Filter icon → aria-label='Filter settings'; Refresh → aria-label='Refresh reviews'.
Chart accessibility	Chart.js charts must include aria-label on <canvas> and a visually hidden data table as fallback.
Focus states	All interactive elements need visible focus rings (focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pink-500 or system default).
Motion sensitivity	Sentiment bar animations and keyword hover effects should respect prefers-reduced-motion: reduce.



